  "text": "In our series of patients, 17 quadrants of biopsy were not diffusion restricted and 13 out of them had Gleason score of 6 (76.4%). This finding is explained by Langer et al., who inferred that sparse tumors had Gleason score of 6, having more water proton diffusibility and similar ADC values as adjacent normal peripheral tissue [CITATION_1] . Tumor visibility and localization were therefore not improved by T2 combined with DWI and ADC maps, in cases of well-differentiated (low-risk) adenocarcinoma [CITATION_2] .",
